{#-
  _auth-shell — centered viewport-min-height layout shell for Auth patterns.

  Composed by Auth-Login, Auth-Register, Auth-ForgotPassword, Auth-ResetPassword
  (Ring 3 S3.1) and every future Auth pattern that needs the same centered-card
  layout (Auth-OTP / MagicLink / EmailVerification / PasswordStrength /
  AccountLocked — Ring 3 S3.1b/c).

  Composition pattern — Twig {% embed %} with blocks:

    {% embed '@theme/components/_auth-shell/_auth-shell.html.twig' with {
      title: 'theme.auth.login.title'|trans,
      subtitle: 'theme.auth.login.subtitle'|trans,
      htmlId: 'auth-login',
    } %}
      {% block brand %}  <a href="/"><img src="/logo.svg" alt="…"></a>  {% endblock %}
      {% block content %}  <form>…</form>  {% endblock %}
      {% block footer %}   <p>Pas encore de compte ? …</p>  {% endblock %}
    {% endembed %}

  Why {% embed %} and NOT {% include with content: '<form>...' %}:
    - The shell hosts arbitrary form Twig (Field / Input / Button composition
      + interpolated server-side CSRF token + per-pattern data-* attributes).
    - {% include with content: "<form>…</form>" %} would force the consumer
      to render the form as a string and pass it via |raw — fragile and
      bypasses Twig autoescape.
    - {% embed %} keeps the form as Twig source under autoescape and aligns
      with the kit's established composition pattern (mirror [Card][1] +
      [Empty][2] Ring 1 keystone).
    - The mini-OQ-53a "include with content" recommendation in S3.1 opening
      was about the SEMANTIC ("include this shared shell, pass it your
      content") — not literal Twig {% include %}. Documented in the S3.1
      session log of `docs/STATE.md`.

    [1] src/templates/components/card/card.html.twig
    [2] src/templates/components/empty/empty.html.twig

  Variants:
    - default — single-column centered. Single panel, no side illustration.
                Mobile-first; the canonical Auth visual.
    - split   — illustration aside + panel side-by-side from ≥ 1024 px.
                Below 1024 px, falls back to single-column (illustration is
                hidden at < 1024 px to preserve form prominence on mobile).

  Layout: see CSS file header for the box model.

  Parameters:
    title       (string, required)         — h1 inside the Card header
    subtitle    (string, optional)         — caption below the h1
    htmlId      (string, optional)         — auto-generated; used for `aria-labelledby`
    variant     (string, optional)         — default | split (default = default)
    className   (string, optional)         — extra utility classes on <main>

  Blocks (all optional except `content`):
    brand        — branded header (consumer logo / wordmark) above the Card
    illustration — side <aside> illustration (only rendered when variant='split')
    content      — REQUIRED — form body (consumers ALWAYS supply this)
    footer       — link block below the form ("Pas encore de compte ?", etc.)

  Accessibility:
    - <main> landmark — the auth screen is the page's primary content.
    - <article aria-labelledby> — the Card's accessible name is the h1 title.
      When `title` is null (terminal patterns like Auth-AccountLocked where
      the inner Empty primitive owns the h1), the aria-labelledby attribute
      is omitted to avoid a dangling ID reference (the Empty inside owns
      its own role=region + aria-labelledby chain so SR users still get
      proper landmark semantics). This conditional was added in S3.1b
      opening (Phase 2) as a forward-compat tweak for Ring 3+ terminal
      patterns that don't have a "page title + sub-section" structure.
    - illustration <aside aria-hidden="true"> — decorative; the title + body
      carry the semantic content.
-#}

{%- set title       = title       | default(null) -%}
{%- set subtitle    = subtitle    | default(null) -%}
{%- set htmlId      = htmlId      | default('theme-auth-shell-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set variant     = variant     | default('default') -%}
{%- set className   = className   | default('') -%}

{%- set _titleId = htmlId ~ '-title' -%}

{%- set _classes = ['theme-auth-shell'] -%}
{%- if variant == 'split' -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge(['theme-auth-shell--split']) -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

<main class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}" data-variant="{{ variant }}">
  {%- if variant == 'split' and block('illustration') is defined and block('illustration') is not empty -%}
    <aside class="theme-auth-shell__illustration" aria-hidden="true">
      {%- block illustration -%}{%- endblock -%}
    </aside>
  {%- endif -%}

  <section class="theme-auth-shell__panel">
    {%- if block('brand') is defined and block('brand') is not empty -%}
      <header class="theme-auth-shell__brand">{%- block brand -%}{%- endblock -%}</header>
    {%- endif -%}

    <article class="theme-card theme-auth-shell__card"{% if title %} aria-labelledby="{{ _titleId }}"{% endif %}>
      {%- if title -%}
        <header class="theme-card__header theme-auth-shell__card-header">
          <h1 id="{{ _titleId }}" class="theme-auth-shell__title">{{ title }}</h1>
          {%- if subtitle -%}<p class="theme-auth-shell__subtitle">{{ subtitle }}</p>{%- endif -%}
        </header>
      {%- endif -%}

      <div class="theme-card__body theme-auth-shell__card-body">
        {%- block content -%}{%- endblock -%}
      </div>

      {%- if block('footer') is defined and block('footer') is not empty -%}
        <footer class="theme-card__footer theme-auth-shell__card-footer">
          {%- block footer -%}{%- endblock -%}
        </footer>
      {%- endif -%}
    </article>
  </section>
</main>
